Inheritance:
  is a mechanism in Java through which one class acquires the properties and methods of another class.
  it is one of the main four pillars of OOPS
Why we should to use it:
  it helps us to reduce the amount of code that we have to write.
  it is more efficient.
  it saves memory
How we can use it:
  we can use the extends keyword after the class name and then the name of the class from which we want to inherit
  the code.

Types of Inheritance:
  Different language support different types of inheritance but 5 of them are very common:
  1)single
  2)multiple leves
  3)